\ norm / frobenius-norm: sqrt of the sum of squared elements (Euclidean/Frobenius).

\ a 3-4-5 vector: L2 length 5
[ 3 4 ] 1 2 matrix norm . cr                          \ 5
[ 3 4 ] 1 2 matrix frobenius-norm . cr                \ 5
\ negative components square away
[ -3 4 ] 1 2 matrix norm . cr                         \ 5
\ single element
[ 7 ] 1 1 matrix norm . cr                            \ 7
\ zero matrix -> 0
2 2 0-matrix norm . cr                                \ 0
\ a 2x2 block: sqrt(1+4+9+16) = sqrt(30)
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix frobenius-norm . cr
\ norm and frobenius-norm agree on a matrix
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix dup norm swap frobenius-norm = . cr   \ 1
\ identity: sqrt(3)
3 identity-matrix frobenius-norm . cr
\ errors on a non-matrix
[ 1 2 ] norm .                                        \ error: not a matrix
"x" frobenius-norm .                                  \ error: not a matrix
